stylometry: Goal seek is used for what-if analysis. We would use goal seek to find an acceptable level of sales in order to make a certain amount of profit after our expenses, when we know the desired result but not the correct input. Data tables provide multiple solutions to one problem in a set which makes it easy to compare different results to find the best solution.  A time when data tables would be used  would be when calculating multiple results in one operation and comparing them, such as the effect of using different levels of fertilizer on the amount of crop yield.
